Will Margin Calls Crash Stocks In 2021? (Stock Market Outlook)

Hello everyone, in todays video I discuss the potential impact of margin calls on the stock market and stocks in general in 2021. Margin calls are in the news today after Archegos Capital lost over $20 billion on margin today. Credit Suisse (CS) lost over 12% on the day when I was recording this video due to billions of dollars in losses to cover the margin call.

Margin calls are what helped fuel the financial crisis, and stock crash of 2008. Margin debt is currently sitting at an all time high in 2021, and if the stock market downtrends or sees some sort of crash in the near future, then all of this margin debt could fuel the downside and add pressure to it.

Hear my thoughts on the stock market outlook in 2021 and in the future years.

The Interpretation Of Financial Statements (Ben Graham)

Hello everyone, I am Daniel Pronk and in todays video I discuss/summarize Benjamin Grahams book The Interpretation of Financial Statements. This book is very in depth and talks about all the figures you will find on financial statements like the Balance sheet, income statement, and cash flow statement. It really gives you a good idea of what all these numbers mean and how to interpret them.

With that said, I think the book was okay but personally I would not recommend it for the money and in the video I also explain why. Regardless, I think Ben Graham is a great author and investor, and I respect him greatly. He is also the author of the Intelligent Investor, which is arguably the best book on investing ever written.

Why Stocks Are Dropping Today || My Thoughts || My Thoughts

Hello everyone, I am Daniel Pronk and in this video I explain why the stock market dropped today, and what analysts are saying about the Democrats potentially winning the senate. Democrats winning the senate could have huge implications on businesses in 2021. They plan on raising corporate tax, which is why stocks like Apple, Amazon, Microsoft, Facebook, etc. were all down today.

They also plan on introducing more government spending, which could lead to more money printing from the FED and potential inflation. This is why Gold is rallying above $1,900 and gold miners like Kirkland, Kinross and Barrick have all seen great days today.

Lastly, Democrats controlling the senate would make it easier for them to pass laws/bills around renewable energy, which would accelerate the growth of clean energy industries.
